summary:
Active in the chemicals, fertilizers, steel industry and power sector for >30 years. Experienced in:
• Project development to realize green hydrogen, ammonia (and ammonia derivatives like urea ammonia nitrate or calcium ammonia nitrate), methanol, DME and kerosene plants;
• Project development to realize projects to convert municipal waste & waste biomass into valuable products like electricity and green molecules;
• Guiding scientist to develop new technologies like solid oxide electrolyser development - SOEC for green hydrogen production (among other in Faraday-lab of TNO/Voltachem), oxy-fuel combustion using H2 instead of CH4 (HyAPC), metal powder oxidation to produce heat and regeneration with green hydrogen (Metalot), electrochemical low temperature CO2 reduction (TNO/Voltachem & Coval Energy) and high temperature SOEC CO2 reduction technologies (TNO/Voltachem and others), methane pyrolysis technologies to produce zero emission hydrogen and pure high value solid carbon (Ember), municipal waste & biomass conversion into valuable products etc. etc.;
• Assessing best way to produce zero CO2 emission hydrogen (PEM, alkaline, SOEC & AEM electrolysis, methane pyrolysis, blue hydrogen solutions or municipal waste/organic material gasification) for specific user cases. Best solution depends on conditions on location, user case and possibilities to import hydrogen (or products);
• Integrating chemicals, fertilizers, energy, steel, cement, waste processing and agricultural plant activities with the focus on reducing CO2 emissions while keeping/improving business case;
• Advising companies in the value chain from renewable electricity to green hydrogen to ammonia/methanol/kerosene on energy transition topics and challenges;

Master (MSc) degree (drs.) inorganic Chemistry (University Utrecht) and a Bachelors degree Business Administration (Hogeschool Rotterdam). 

Geographic focus area Latin America, Africa and Europe (including Ukraine, Azerbaijan, etc.).

