HyAPC is the new generation oxy-fuel combustion technology which can use methane, hydrogen and even ammonia as a fuel to produce zero CO2 emission electricity. Some of the advantages:
- No CO2 formation in case ammonia or hydrogen is used as a fuel;
- NO CO2 capture processes needed because pure CO2 is produced when using methane as a fuel;
- Efficiency higher than conventional natural gas fired power plants or conventional oxy-fuel plants;
- Low CAPEX, low OPEX;
- No NOx formation;
- Can be installed in existing natural gas fired power plants.

Commercially available in 2027

